Kris Zyp wrote:
&gt; 
&gt; Do you suggest rel=&quot;profile&quot; as preferable to rel=&quot;describedby&quot; for
&gt; referring to a schema for a document?
&gt; 

I&#39;d suggest standardizing rel=&#39;schema&#39;, where @type tells us what the
schema language and its serialization (think RELAX NG compact vs. XML)
are, and @href tells us what the schema itself is.

Schema languages like yours or XSD both impart more semantics to the
content than RELAX NG (which is strictly syntax), but not enough to
warrant describedby -- which means that the document is self-described
(in the SemWeb, RDF sense seen in Tim&#39;s architecture notes) by some
other document conforming to some serialization of RDF, but not as a
syntax validation model.

-Eric
